title: Nitrate Explorer Guide
text: short vignette explains use NitrateExplorer package. package helps explore NEON surface-water nitrate data. gives interactive plots simple summaries. vignette shows load data, make common plots, run Shiny app.

title: Nitrate Explorer Guide
text: NitrateExplorer package includes: Interactive Shiny application data exploration Data processing functions statistical analysis Visualization tools time series distribution analysis Quality-controlled dataset NEON monitoring sites examples use functions package.

title: Nitrate Explorer Guide
text: want run examples computer, install package follow steps . data nitrate_clean cleaned included package. cleaning script data-raw/Nitrate-surface.R.

title: Nitrate Explorer Guide
text: package uses data NEON (National Ecological Observatory Network), specifically “Nitrate Surface Water” product (DP1.20033.001). data quality-filtered include measurements passed quality checks (finalQF = 0). main variables simple: siteID: site code samples taken. startDate: date sampling. surfWaterNitrateMean: average nitrate concentration (mg/L). finalQF: quality flag (0 = pass, 1 = fail). n: number measurements used. can find full data dictionary package app.

title: Nitrate Explorer Guide
text: run app installed package: app lets : choose sites date range, change aggregation (daily / monthly / yearly), change plot type (time series, boxplot, distribution), download filtered data current plot. Inside app, check Data Dictionary tab field meanings. Also read Plot Guidance box quick interpretation tips.
code: # run_nitrate_app()

text: can install package GitHub. Run R: can install development version NitrateExplorer GitHub :
code: # install remotes if you do not have it if (!requireNamespace("remotes", quietly = TRUE)) install.packages("remotes")   # install the package from GitHub (replace with your repo) remotes::install_github("ETC5523-2025/assignment-4-packages-and-shiny-apps-Jing0922") # install.packages("pak") pak::pak("ETC5523-2025/assignment-4-packages-and-shiny-apps-Jing0922")

title: Explore and Visualize NEON Surface Water Nitrate Data
text: install, run: open interactive app. app lets choose sites, dates, plot types. also allows download filtered data plots.
code: library(NitrateExplorer) # run_nitrate_app()

title: Explore and Visualize NEON Surface Water Nitrate Data
text: package includes main functions: run_app(): launch Shiny app. calculate_daily_stats(data) — return daily summaries. calculate_monthly_stats(data) — return monthly summaries. calculate_yearly_stats(data) — return yearly summaries. plot_time_series(agg_data, sites, aggregation) — draw time series plot aggregated data. boxplot_comparison(data, sites) — draw boxplots compare sites. plot_distribution(data, sites, bin_size, show_density, facet_sites) — draw distribution plot. functions documented. See man/ folder details examples.

title: Explore and Visualize NEON Surface Water Nitrate Data
text: package includes nitrate_clean dataset containing quality-controlled nitrate measurements NEON sites. saved usethis::use_data() data/. using data, please cite NEON appropriately according data use policies. Key fields: siteID: ARIK, COMO, KING, LEWI, MAYF startDate: date sample. surfWaterNitrateMean: nitrate concentration (mg/L). finalQF: quality flag (0 = pass). n: number measurements. cleaning script data-raw/Nitrate-surface.R.
